# Configuration

Vyro Shops uses a simple and intuitive configuration structure defined in `Config.lua`.

## Config.lua Structure

The Config.lua file contains all your shop definitions:

```lua
Config = {}

-- Your shop definitions go here
Config.Shops = {
    shop_name_here = {
        shopName = "Display Name",
        items = {
            {name = "item_name", price = 100},
            {name = "another_item", price = 50}
        },
        -- Additional configuration options
    }
}
```

## Shop Configuration Format

Each shop entry should follow this structure:

```lua
shop_identifier = {
    shopName = "Shop Display Name",      -- Name shown to players
    items = {
        {
            name = "item_name",           -- Item identifier
            price = 100                    -- Sale price
        }
    }
}
```

## Tips

- Use the **Shop Maker UI** to generate proper configurations automatically
- Export your completed shops and paste them directly into Config.lua
- Item names must match identifiers in your inventory system (ox_inventory or qb-core)
- The UI handles all formatting, reducing configuration errors
